OL,3,CThe hunt for the 'heavy bag man'
OL,4,Cmurderer
OL,6,FBut Majerkiewicz had hugely
OL,7,Funderestimated the capabilities of
OL,8,Fdetectives from Greater Manchester
OL,9,FPolice.
OL,11,FWhen Stuart's torso and thighs were
OL,12,Fdiscovered at a remote nature reserve
OL,13,Faround a week after he was murdered, a
OL,14,Fhuge investigation was launched.
OL,16,FOfficers had no clue who the victim
OL,17,Fwas, but they began to work on the
OL,18,Ffollowing hypothesis; whoever dumped
OL,19,Fthe remains must have done so on foot,
OL,20,Fas it's not possible to drive up to
OL,21,Fthat area of the park.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
